Old Value: 1) Identity & alias set: The query gives "GROUND SERVICES INTERNATIONAL, INC. DBA: DNATA" at an Orlando, FL airport-operations address. dnata is a well-known global air and ground services brand; in the U.S. its ground-handling subsidiaries commonly use dnata as the operating/brand name and appear as DBAs linked to the global dnata group. Public profiles for "dnata" consistently describe one global enterprise providing ground handling, cargo, travel, and catering services across multiple continents, matching the described airport-operations business. 2) Current operating name: ZoomInfo shows a single consolidated company profile under the brand "Dnata" with website www.dnata.com and describes it as a global air services provider, which is consistent with the DBA name and business description. 3) Identity verification: We can confidently match on (a) name/alias: dnata vs. dnata DBA; and (b) industry/description: airport operations / aircraft ground handling and related air services; and (c) global enterprise structure where U.S. ground-service entities operate under dnata branding. The specific Orlando address appears to be a U.S. location of the same employing group rather than a separate non-dnata business. 4) Maturity: dnata was founded in 1959, which is >40 years, placing it in maturity class D with a floor of 75 employees. 5) Source prioritization and counts: ZoomInfo (priority source) lists dnata under Airlines, Airports & Air Services with a clearly labeled headcount of "39,000 Employees". This is a direct numeric employee count for the same global entity and is well above the class-D floor and consistent with other public descriptions of dnata as a large global operator. No ZoomInfo or Growjo record was found that would more specifically and reliably represent only a tiny U.S. Orlando sub-entity; given the instructions not to switch entities and the fact that the DBA aligns with the global profile, the appropriate unit of analysis is the dnata group entity as represented on ZoomInfo. 6) Outlier/consensus: The 39,000-employee figure on ZoomInfo is not contradicted by any other prioritized source and sits comfortably within the expected size range for a global multi-continent ground-handling and catering provider. Therefore ZoomInfo is deemed usable per the rules, and its employee count can be adopted without adjustment. 7) Final selection and floor check: Using the ZoomInfo figure of 39,000 employees satisfies the requirement that the selected employee_count not be below the maturity-class D floor of 75; no floor-based fallback is needed.
New Value: The provided details (DBA 7-ELEVEN store, convenience retail, Los Angeles, CA) clearly refer to a local franchise/unit of the global 7-Eleven convenience store chain, whose current operating/brand name is 7-Eleven, Inc., commonly branded as 7-Eleven. Alias set: 7-Eleven, 7-Eleven, Inc., 7-ELEVEN, 7 - eleven, 7-eleven inc, 7-ELEVEN NO: 2173-18463C (DBA). Identity is verified by matching the name/DBA and business type (convenience retail) with the global 7-Eleven corporate entity. ZoomInfo lists 7-Eleven corporate office at 3200 Hackberry Rd, Irving, TX and reports that it "has 45,000 employees," which is a clear numeric global headcount but appears lower than multiple other reputable estimates. Growjo estimates 67,755 employees. Wikipedia reports 135,332 employees for 7-Eleven. These are all for the same global brand/entity, not the specific Los Angeles store. Applying the rules: ZoomInfo is the primary source and provides a usable numeric count (45,000). However, it is more than 2Ã lower than the Wikipedia figure and materially below the Growjo estimate, suggesting it may undercount (e.g., excluding franchise staff). With ZoomInfo in tension with other reputable sources, I look for a consensus band: Growjo (67,755) and Wikipedia (135,332) are both â¥ the maturity floor and represent a plausible range for total global headcount. Choosing a value within that credible range and not below the lowest, I select a rounded, conservative figure of 75,000, which sits between ZoomInfo and the higher external estimates and respects the requirement that the count be at or above the appropriate maturity floor. 7-Eleven was founded in 1927 (originally Totem Stores), placing it well over 40 years old; therefore, maturity class is D and the minimum floor is 75 employees. The final employee_count (75,000) is far above this floor and consistent with a large, mature, global convenience retail chain. Because both ZoomInfo and Growjo provide usable numeric counts for the same entity and geography, a floor-based fallback is not needed; instead, I use a consensus-informed value constrained by the rules and maturity floor.
